reviewText: "Fake Preacher" is a very entertaining film.  I caught an description on the net, advertising that this low-budget film was a comedy, however I felt that it was very poignant.  Being from Harlem, New York, where on every block there's a church, I've often wondered how many of these church preachers were really teaching the gospel and not just ripping off their parishioners.  The feature deals with a subject few would talk about.  Peachers' who con their church members to line their pockets.  This film centers around a con man who does just that.  However in the end, he gets his up and comings, which once again demonstrates good always triumphs over evil.  I thought the acting was good and they did have some, comedy in the film, however I thought the star, Eddie Goeins standed out among all the rest. I recommend this film, specially to Christians who are still looking for a church.  beware, there are really some fake preachers out there.
